# Browser-visible API base (no trailing slash on version path)
# Local dev API default port 8001; production uses 8000.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8001/api

# Optional: use `apps/web/.env.local` (gitignored) for real Supabase keys.

# Local Supabase (from `supabase start` — Project URL / APIs)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# Publishable (anon) key — copy from `supabase status` (do not commit real keys to git)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Google OAuth via Supabase (PKCE — recommended):
# - Google Cloud "Authorized redirect URIs" must include your Supabase callback
#   (see Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Google), e.g.
#   http://127.0.0.1:54321/auth/v1/callback for local `supabase start`.
# - Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL configuration → Redirect URLs must include:
#     http://localhost:3002/auth/callback
#     (add production app URL when deployed; must match `redirectTo` in `signInWithOAuth`).
# - `signInWithOAuth({ provider: 'google', options: { redirectTo, scopes, queryParams } })`:
#     redirectTo: full URL to this app’s `/auth/callback` (see `apps/web/app/auth/page.tsx`).
#     queryParams: { access_type: 'offline', prompt: 'consent' } so Google returns a refresh token.
#     scopes: see `apps/web/lib/google-oauth.ts` (openid, profile, contacts.readonly, calendar.readonly).
# - After `exchangeCodeForSession`, the server route calls the Nest API `link-provider`; the user
#   must already have Contactbook API cookies (`cb_access_token`) from WhatsApp sign-in.
